Subject: [PATCH] mpc8536ds: Wake up on GPIO

MPC8536DS can be wakeup from sleep mode via GPIO pin.
Add GPIO pin in device tree.

[
>>From e3f782a5cdb4489eff96cab7a7eed9c7db1e0249 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dave Liu <daveliu@freescale.com>
Date: Fri, 11 Jul 2008 14:47:42 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Wake up on GPIO

GPIO14 acts as wake up source from sleep/deep sleep

Signed-off-by: Dave Liu <daveliu@freescale.com>
]
Integrated-by: Thomas Tai <thomas.tai@windriver.com>
---
 arch/powerpc/boot/dts/mpc8536ds.dts |    7 +++++++
 1 files changed, 7 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/mpc8536ds.dts b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/mpc8536ds.dts
index ae2f31c..ce4bc7e 100644
--- a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/mpc8536ds.dts
+++ b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/mpc8536ds.dts
@@ -324,6 +324,13 @@
 			reg = <0xe0070 0x20>;
 		};
 
+		gpio@fc00 {
+			compatible = "fsl,mpc8536-gpio";
+			reg = <0xfc00 0x100>;
+			interrupts = <47 2>;
+			interrupt-parent = <&mpic>;
+		};
+
 		mpic: pic@40000 {
 			clock-frequency = <0>;
 			interrupt-controller;
-- 
